The new version of Chai has moved nested properties from syntax like

```
const v = { a: { b: 'potato' } };
expect(v).to.have.deep.property('a.b', 'potato');
```

to

```
const v = { a: { b: 'potato' } };
expect(v).to.have.nested.property('a.b', 'potato');
```

to disambiguate the meaning of 'deep' into `deep` === 'deep equality' and `nested` === 'deep property name'.

Note that I just took a stab at adding the .nested selector for 4.0 (this is what I'm using for the time being at least), because I didn't want to break backwards compatibility on the types library for 3.5 users.
